{
  "texts": [
    "Traditional olfactory analysis often assumes a one-size-fits-all approach, but human sensory perception varies widely across individuals due to factors such as genetic differences, health conditions, and personal experiences.",
    "To address this, AI systems are now being developed to integrate individual-specific data, such as genetic predispositions (e.g., variations in olfactory receptors), age, and even lifestyle factors.",
    "For instance, recent studies have explored the integration of genetic data with olfactory profiles to predict an individual's sensitivity to specific odors (Achebouche et al. 2022).",
    "These personalized models can be used to predict how different individuals will perceive the same odorant, thereby improving the accuracy of odor classification and enhancing consumer experiences in industries like fragrance and food.",
    "By training AI systems on personalized datasets, these models can offer more precise recommendations for fragrance or flavor products, leading to higher customer satisfaction and product acceptance."
  ]
}